=SET TIMEZONE = 'Asia/Kuala_Lumpur';

select A.*,
to_char(cft.cft,'YYYY-MM') as cft_month
from 
(select distinct l.id, 
l.registration_no, 
case when ll.city_id in (1) then 'KV'   
when ll.city_id in (2,12) then 'PGM' when ll.city_id in (48) then 'PGI'
when ll.city_id in (3,19,20,21) then 'KK'   when ll.city_id in (4) then 'JB' 
when ll.city_id in (5) then 'IP'   when ll.city_id in (47) then 'NS'
when ll.city_id in (13) then 'LGK' 
when ll.city_id in (14) then 'PRLS'
when ll.city_id in (15) then 'MLK'
when ll.city_id in (16) then 'PHG'
when ll.city_id in (17) then 'TRGN'
when ll.city_id in (18) then 'KLT'
when ll.city_id in (22,23) then 'KCH'
else 'Others' end as City,
to_char(l.created_at::timestamp,'YYYY-MM-DD') as created_at,
to_char(l.created_at::timestamp,'YYYY-MM') as created_at_month,
case when l.first_approved_at is null then to_char(l.approved_at,'YYYY-MM') else to_char(l.first_approved_at,'YYYY-MM') end as approved_at,
l.user_id, 
concat(u.first_name,' ', u.last_name)as host_name, 
case when t.name like 'SC -%' then t.name else null end as tag, 
case when t.name like 'SC -%' then t.updated_at else null end as tag_updated
from listings l 
left join tag_taggables tt on tt.taggable_id = l.id 
left join tags t on t.id = tt.tag_id 
left join users u on u.id = l.user_id
left join (select distinct listing_id, country, city_id from listing_location) ll on ll.listing_id = l.id
where 1=1
and ll.country = 'Malaysia'
and l.status = 'approved'
and l.deleted_at is null)A
        --
        left join 
        (select distinct l.id,  
        max(t.updated_at::timestamp) as max_updated_at 
        from listings l 
        left join tag_taggables tt on tt.taggable_id = l.id 
        left join tags t on t.id = tt.tag_id 
        where (t.name like 'SC -%')
        group by 1)B
        on B.id = A.id and B.max_updated_at = A.tag_updated 
        --
        left join
        (select distinct b.listing_id, 
        min(b.request_end_at::timestamp) as cft
        from bookings b 
        where b.status = 'completed'
        group by 1)cft
        on cft.listing_id = A.id
where B.max_updated_at is not null
order by 1

=SET TIMEZONE = 'Asia/Kuala_Lumpur';

--active booking months
select distinct A.month,
A.listing_id
from
(select distinct b.listing_id,
dates.ymd, 
to_char(dates.ymd,'YYYY-MM') as month
from bookings b 
left join listing_location ll on ll.listing_id = b.listing_id 
join (SELECT generate_series(timestamp '2024-01-01', '2025-12-31' , interval '1 day')::date as ymd) dates 
on dates.ymd between b.request_start_at::timestamp and b.request_end_at::timestamp
where b.status in ('completed','start_driving','waiting_for_inspection', 'return_car')
and ll.country = 'Malaysia')A

=SET TIMEZONE = 'Asia/Kuala_Lumpur';

SELECT DISTINCT u.id, t.name
FROM users u
LEFT JOIN tag_taggables tt ON tt.taggable_id = u.id
LEFT JOIN tags t ON t.id = tt.tag_id
WHERE t.name LIKE 'SC -%'
AND u.id IN (
    SELECT CAST(substring(t.name from '\[(\d+)\]') AS INTEGER) AS catalyst_id
    FROM tags t
    WHERE t.name LIKE 'CT -%')

=SET TIMEZONE = 'Asia/Kuala_Lumpur';

select distinct l.id, l.registration_no, 
to_char(l.deleted_at, 'YYYY-MM')as deleted_month
from listings l 
left join listing_location ll on ll.listing_id = l.id
where ll.country = 'Malaysia'
and l.deleted_at is not null
order by 2
